# A/B (dual-bank) partition layout for the IoT RPi image (RAUC, Phase 2).
# See apps/docs/tdd-ab-image-ota.md §2.  device-bring-up scaffold — validate on HW.
#
#   p1 boot   (FAT)  bootloader + per-bank kernel/dtb + boot-select env
#   p2 rootA  (ext4) rootfs bank A   ─┐ only the INACTIVE bank is written on update
#   p3 rootB  (ext4) rootfs bank B   ─┘ (atomic + power-fail-safe; active keeps running)
#   p4 data   (ext4) persistent: mounted at /var/lib/private (ds StateDirectory)
#
# Enabled by an A/B build: WKS_FILE="iot-ab.wks.in" (set in entrypoint.sh /
# kas-ab.yml when IOT_AB=1). Needs RPI_USE_U_BOOT=1 — u-boot's boot.cmd
# (meta-rauc-raspberrypi) selects the bank by partition number (mmc 0:2 → p2 =
# bank A, mmc 0:3 → p3 = bank B), matching /etc/rauc/system.conf.
#
# /boot is 100M: holds the RPi firmware + u-boot.bin + boot.scr + the u-boot
# fw_env, with headroom (the per-bank kernel/dtb live in each rootfs /boot,
# loaded by u-boot from the active bank).
#
# EVERY partition carries `--no-fstab-update` so wic NEVER writes /etc/fstab —
# base-files (recipes-core/base-files bbappend) is the SOLE fstab authority.
# Without it, wic's --fstab-update appends entries using /dev/sdaN device names
# (e.g. `/dev/sda1 /boot`, `/dev/sda4 /var/lib/iot`) — devices that DON'T EXIST
# on an mmc-booted RPi. The /dev/sda4 entry self-bricks the image: local-fs
# waits ~90s then drops to emergency mode (and on A/B BOTH banks brick). This is
# injected at do_image_wic, AFTER do_rootfs and after the iot-image.bb fstab
# precheck (which only sees the rootfs fstab), so it ships silently — HW-hit
# repeatedly during bring-up. The mmcblk0p1 /boot mount comes from base-files.
#
# The data partition (p4, LABEL=data) is mounted at /var/lib/private — NOT via
# fstab (kept clean) but by the shipped `var-lib-private.mount` systemd unit
# (recipes-iot/lwm2m). That is where iot-ds's DynamicUser StateDirectory=iot
# state (data_store.lua = all operator config) actually lands, so mounting the
# persistent partition there is what makes config (wifi.networks, PSKs, endpoint
# creds) SURVIVE a RAUC A/B bank swap. It must be /var/lib/private, NOT
# /var/lib/iot — a mount at the latter collides with the StateDirectory symlink
# and crash-loops iot-ds (exit 238/STATE_DIRECTORY, HW-confirmed). The `part`
# mountpoint below is cosmetic (--no-fstab-update ⇒ wic writes no fstab entry).

# Bank size (1024M) must exceed the standalone rootfs ext4 RAUC carries in the
# .raucb — that image is inflated by IMAGE_ROOTFS_EXTRA_SPACE (512M of on-target
# headroom for opkg/logs) to ~824M, and `rauc install` writes it raw to the
# inactive slot. 768M banks flash fine (wic builds them from the rootfs dir,
# ~300M used) but an OTA into a 768M slot would fail "image larger than slot".
part /boot --source bootimg-partition --fstype=vfat --label boot --active --align 4096 --size 100M --no-fstab-update
part /     --source rootfs --fstype=ext4 --label rootA --align 4096 --size 1024M --no-fstab-update
part /     --source rootfs --fstype=ext4 --label rootB --align 4096 --size 1024M --no-fstab-update
part /var/lib/private --fstype=ext4 --label data --align 4096 --size 256M --no-fstab-update

bootloader --ptable msdos
